  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. A key requirement mandates experimental-validation as the verification method for hemolysis QoI confirmation; however, the supporting validation activity was conducted via numerical-simulation (high-fidelity parametric sweep). The narrative characterises the simulation sweep as functionally equivalent to bench testing given the validated boundary conditions, but the structured activityType field disagrees with the requiredVerificationMethod declared on the bound Requirement, creating an undercutting inference-method mismatch (W-AR-03). Decision is recorded as Accepted on the basis of the narrative argument.",
