    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team accepted the package on the basis that the high-fidelity parametric CFD sweep, anchored by experimentally characterised boundary conditions from a prior study, provides hemolysis predictions with sufficient confidence for the intended regulatory submission. The team argued the numerical simulation is functionally equivalent to bench experimental validation given the quality of the boundary condition data and the Monte Carlo uncertainty bands. The structured Requirement node (req/vad-hemolysis-verification) specifies requiredVerificationMethod: experimental-validation, but the sole ValidationResult was generated by an Activity with activityType: numerical-simulation. This inference-method mismatch (W-AR-03) is not surfaced in the narrative argument and the package is accepted without resolving it.",
